criteria.textblock:
        Key Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Planned routine cataract surgery in at least one eye;

          -  Calculated lens power within the available range;

          -  Willing and able to sign an informed consent statement;

          -  Clear intraocular media other than cataract.

        Key Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Any disease or pathology, other than cataract, that is expected to reduce the
             potential postoperative best corrected distance visual acuity (BCDVA) to a level worse
             than 0.30 logMAR;

          -  Previous corneal surgery;

          -  Rubella or traumatic cataract;

          -  Ocular trauma, previous refractive surgery;

          -  Current or recent use of certain medications as specified in the protocol;

          -  Any other ocular or systemic condition that, in the opinion of the Investigator,
             should exclude the subject from the study.
